---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from "../consts.ts";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import heroImg from "../assets/images/Jesus-Divine-Mercy.webp";
const title = `Prayers | ${SITE_TITLE}`;
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}>
  <Hero
    title="Praying for Francis"
    subtitle="Journey with us in praying for Francis"
    imageSrc={heroImg.src}
  />
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Pray With Us</h2>
      <p>
        Throughout Francis’s journey, prayer has been at the center of
        everything. It's been instrumental in keeping us grounded as a family,
        helping us rely on God and turning to him in our hardest moments. We
        have witnessed the power of God working through the prayers of so many
        who have said they are praying for Francis.
      </p>
      <p>We prayed to many different saints, some of whom w</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our Litany of Saints</h2>
      <p>
        During some of our hardest moments, we prayed to many different saints who are listed below.
        Some of them we have a particular devotion to as a family, such as St. Therese and her parents, Saints Zelie and Louis. Others
        we came to know through the suggestion of family and friends. We also implored the intercession of our own family members, including one holy man in particular, Thomas Vander Woude. We believe his intercession played a pivotal role in Francis' healing and miraculous recovery.
      </p>
  
      <ul>
        <li>Roy Hollis</li>
        <li>Thomas Vanderwoude</li>
        <li>Pope Francis</li>
        <li>St. Therese</li>
        <li>Sts. Zelie and Louis</li>
        <li>St. Francis of Assisi</li>
        <li>St. Clare of Assisi</li>
        <li>St. Francis Xavier</li>
        <li>St. Francis De Sales</li>
        <li>St. John Baptist de Rossi</li>
        <li>St. Vitus</li>
        <li>St. Valentine</li>
        <li>Venerable Fulton Sheen</li>
        <li>St. Padre Pio of Pietrelcina</li>
        <li>Blessed John Licci</li>
        <li>Blessed Carlo Acutis</li>
        <li>St. Dymphna</li>
        <li>Baby Francis Kuisell</li>
        <li>Baby Samuel Kuisell</li>
        <li>Quenum Babies</li>
        <li>Baby Hyacinth Armstrong</li>
        <li>Baby Christopher Rea</li>
        <li>Baby Maximillian Pietrandrea</li>
        <li>Baby Sebastian Pietrandrea</li>
        <li>Baby Emmanuel Trebing</li>
        <li>John Francis Cannon</li>
        <li>Donald Lilly</li>
        <li>Mama Noone</li>
        <li>John Clem</li>
        <li>Nicolas Adinaro</li>
      </ul>

       <p>
    In the Catholic Church, saints are men and women who have lived lives of extraordinary holiness and are believed
      to be in Heaven with God. As Catholics, we ask for their intercession and their prayers, trusting that they are close to God and are praying for us.
    </p>
 
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="prayer-form">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Submit a Prayer Request</h2>
      <p>We would be honored to pray for you. Share your intention below.</p>

      <form
        name="prayer-requests"
        method="POST"
        data-netlify="true"
        netlify-honeypot="bot-field"
        class="p-6 sm:p-8 space-y-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-md">
        <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="prayer-requests" />

        <p class="hidden">
          <label>
            Don’t fill this out if you're human:
            <input name="bot-field" />
          </label>
        </p>

        <!-- Name -->
        <div>
          <label
            for="name"
            class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
            Name
          </label>
          <input
            type="text"
            name="name"
            id="name"
            required
            class="peer w-full px-3 pt-5 pb-2 bg-transparent border border-gray-200 shadow-sm rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-blue-300 text-base leading-relaxed"
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Email -->
        <div>
          <label
            for="email"
            class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
            Email
          </label>
          <input
            type="email"
            name="email"
            id="email"
            required
            class="peer w-full px-3 pt-5 pb-2 bg-transparent border border-gray-200 shadow-sm rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-blue-300 text-base leading-relaxed"
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Prayer Request -->
        <div>
          <label
            for="request"
            class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
            Prayer Request
          </label>
          <textarea
            name="request"
            id="request"
            rows="5"
            required
            class="peer w-full px-3 pt-5 pb-2 bg-transparent border border-gray-200 shadow-sm rounded-lg focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-blue-300 resize-none text-base leading-relaxed"
          ></textarea>
        </div>

        <!-- Button -->
        <button
          type="submit"
          class="py-3 px-4 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-transparent text-gray-800 text-base font-medium hover:bg-white/10 transition focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-blue-300">
          Submit
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
<style>
  main {
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  input,
  textarea {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .hidden {
    display: none;
  }
</style>
